# Telegram Cloud: Project Files Overview

This document provides a detailed explanation of each file in the `telegram-cloud` project and an assessment of whether the codebase is up to date.

## 📂 Core Logic & Backend

| File | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| [bot.py](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/bot.py) | The main entry point for the Web application (Flask). It handles user authentication, routing, and coordinates file operations using the [BotActions](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/core.py#21-256) class. |
| [core.py](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/core.py) | Contains the core logic of the application. It includes [BotActions](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/core.py#21-256) for Telegram API interactions, [SchemaManipulations](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/core.py#258-405) for managing the virtual file system, and [EncDecHelper](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/core.py#407-431) for file encryption/decryption. |
| [utils/functions.py](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/utils/functions.py) | Contains utility functions, notably [manage_file_shares](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/utils/functions.py#7-26), which runs in a background thread to enforce expiry limits on shared files. |
| [backupper.py](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/backupper.py) | A CLI tool built with `click` for bulk uploading local directories to Telegram and bulk downloading folders from Telegram back to local storage. |
| [exp.py](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/exp.py) | An experimental script using the `Telethon` library. It appears to be a draft for bypassing the 50MB Bot API limit by using the MTProto API (Telegram User API). |

## 🌐 Web Interface (templates/ & static/)

- **`templates/`**: Contains Jinja2 HTML templates for the Flask app.
    - [index.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/index.html): The main dashboard for browsing files and folders.
    - [login.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/login.html): Simple login page.
    - [navbar.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/navbar.html): Reusable navigation bar.
    - [bulk-upload.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/bulk-upload.html): Interface for bulk operations.
    - [flash.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/flash.html): Handles alert messages (success/error).
    - [recovery.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/recovery.html): Interface for schema recovery.
    - [error.html](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Documents/projects/telegram-cloud/templates/error.html): Generic error display page.
- **`static/`**: Contains CSS, JavaScript, and icons used for styling the web interface.

